All first-principles computations were performed based on density-functional theory (DFT) methods as implemented in the Vienna ab initio simulation package (VASP 5.4). An energy cutoff of 520 eV was employed, and the atomic positions were optimized using PBEsol functional until the maximum force on each atom was less than 0.02 eV∙Å–1. The ion cores were described by using the projector-augmented wave (PAW) method. A 4 × 4 × 4 k-point grid was used for the mixed perovskites. The simulation cells of mixed perovskites with different stoichiometry containing eight units were constructed by replacing the corresponding Sn(II) or Ge(II). For each composition, the geometry and cell length were then fully relaxed. This justifies the estimation of the entropy-of-mixing contribution to the free energy by using the analytical formula for ideal alloys: TΔS=-kBTxlnx+1-xln1-x\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
